text: Patrice de MacMahon, 6th Marquess of MacMahon, 1st Duke of Magenta (; born Marie Edme Patrice Maurice; 13 June 1808 – 17 October 1893), was a French general and politician. He was Chief of State of France from 1873 to 1875 and as President of France, from 1875 to 1879. ==References== Category:1808 births Category:1893 deaths Category:Presidents of France Category:People from Saône- et-Loire Category:Politicians from Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes Category:19th-century presidents of France
title: Patrice de MacMahon
